{{EngvarB|date=September 2017}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}} {{Infobox Radio station |name = Radio Rivers FM |image = |city = [[Port Harcourt]] |area = [[Rivers State]] |frequency = 99.1 [[Megahertz|MHz]] FM |airdate = 2 May 1981 |format = |language = Mixed [[Indigenous language|indigenous]] and [[English language|English]] |power = |coordinates = {{Coord|4|49|46|N|7|4|31|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} |owner = [[Rivers State government|RSG]] |website = }}
'''Radio Rivers 99.1''' (also known as '''Radio Rivers 2''') is the first [[state-owned]] [[Frequency modulation|FM]] [[List of radio stations in Port Harcourt|radio station]] in [[Rivers State]], and the second FM radio station to launch in [[Nigeria]]. It is run by [[Rivers State Broadcasting Corporation]] (RSBC) and operates on 99.1 [[Megahertz]]. The station first signed on the air on Saturday 2 May 1981.<ref name="radio rivers"/>
Radio Rivers FM's studios are based in the [[Port Harcourt]] neighborhood of [[Elelenwo, Port Harcourt|Elelenwo]] from where it transmits to various towns and municipalities of the state.<ref name="elelenwo1">{{cite web|url=http://www.thetidenewsonline.com/2012/01/20/thieves-invade-elelenwo-station-of-radio-rivers-cart-away-gen-set-parts/|title=Thieves Invade Elelenwo Station Of Radio Rivers …Cart Away Gen Set Parts|publisher=''[[The Tide (Nigeria)|The Tide]]''|date=2012-01-20 |accessdate=2014-06-29}}</ref>
==Programming== Radio Rivers has a broad range of programming. This includes news and information (particularly on the native ethnic groups of Rivers State who don't receive wider coverage on other stations), local sport, music, arts and culture and public announcements. It is the only major radio station existing that is devoted to promoting Riverians and their local vernacular languages.<ref name="radio rivers">{{cite news|url=http://www.thetidenewsonline.com/2014/05/07/radio-rivers-at-33/|title=Radio Rivers At 33 |date=2014-05-07|work=[[The Tide (Nigeria)|The Tide]]|language=|location=[[Port Harcourt]], [[Nigeria]]|publisher=Rivers State Newspaper Corporation|accessdate=2014-06-29}}</ref> <ref name="RR 99.1">{{cite web|url=https://www.academia.edu/5034279/Audience_Assessment_of_News_Commentary_on_Radio_Rivers_99.1FM_A_Port_Harcourt_City_Survey|title=Audience Assessment of News Commentary on Radio Rivers 99.1FM: A Port Harcourt City Survey|last=Uwalaka|first=Temple|work=[[Academia.edu]]|format=PDF|date= |accessdate=2014-05-17}}</ref>
